  The shootout between the robbers and the police ensued after the SAPS received a tip off that a gang of robbers were planning to target a number of ATM’s in Mhluzi.
One ATM was bombed before police confronted the robbers and a shootout ensued. Also read: Three killed in shootout with Police A high speed chase then led to the old Witbank road where another shootout ensued. High calibre assault rifles were used by the robbers including AK47 and R5 rifles.
A number of them fled on food into the surrounding rural area. Also read: #TrafficUpdate: N4 traffic increases due to early morning shootout between police and robbers Residents on small holdings and farms on the R555 are advised to be on the lookout for suspicious people.
The road remains closed for traffic while the search for the suspects continues. *** This is an unfolding story. Stay tuned on www.mobserver.co.za for updates. Suspects might be linked to seven other robberies • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za